  "body": "See screenshot below which shows beta 7 next to the relevant Figma design.\r\n\r\n![replies to comments UI implementation doesn't match design](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22846356/112508412-6b959a80-8d87-11eb-928a-f4f128d7bd42.png)\r\n\r\nThe primary issues in the implementation are:\r\n- the text at the top of the reply bubble (the \"-> @[name]\" text and the quoted comment text) is the wrong colour.\r\n- the separator line is the wrong colour \r\n- the \"-> @[name]\" text at the top of the bubble should be the same size as quoted comment text size\r\n- the margins of text at the top of the reply bubble and the reply itself don't match up (they should be the same)\r\n- the expand button in the implementation doesn't seem to match the figma design, see screenshot below\r\n![2021-03-25 16_40_53-ðŸ’¬ ChatâŽœDesktop - Figma](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22846356/112510013-f034e880-8d88-11eb-8e61-0b53bd751e0a.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIt's also worth checking that the font sizes match with the design.  Difficult for me to tell if the font sizes are correct in the implementation due the the scaling issues ( #2124 ) on Windows.",
